  "prompt": "How do I create a page for a company in Wikipedia?",
  "response": "Creating a Wikipedia page for a company involves several steps and guidelines:\n\n1. Notability Requirements\n- The company must meet Wikipedia's notability standards\n- Must have significant independent media coverage\n- Coverage should be from reliable, third-party sources\n- Not just press releases or company-generated content\n\n2. Preliminary Steps\n- Create a Wikipedia account\n- Review Wikipedia's conflict of interest guidelines\n- Gather reliable sources about the company\n- Ensure sources are from independent, reputable publications\n\n3. Draft Creation\n- Start by creating a draft in Wikipedia's draft namespace\n- Use neutral, encyclopedic language\n- Include verifiable information\n- Cite sources using footnotes\n- Include sections like company history, products/services, leadership\n\n4. Source Requirements\n- Use multiple independent sources\n- Prefer academic, news, and professional publications\n- Avoid using the company's own website or marketing materials as primary sources\n\n5. Submission Process\n- Once draft is complete, submit for review\n- Experienced editors will evaluate the page\n- Be prepared to make suggested revisions\n- Page might be rejected if it doesn't meet guidelines\n\n6. Important Tips\n- Be transparent about your connection to the company\n- Focus on factual, neutral information\n- Follow Wikipedia's core content policies\n\nProfessional assistance or consultation might be helpful in navigating the process.",
